    <avalancheActivity>
      <highlights>A lot of snow fell in the past few hours. Towards its surface, the snowpack is unstable.</highlights>
      <comment>Over a wide area 40 to 60 cm of snow, and even more in some localities, fell yesterday above approximately 2000 m. &lt;br/> The new snow of yesterday can be released easily or naturally especially on steep sunny slopes. &lt;br/> Above approximately 2200 m: The covering of new snow is weak. Avalanches can be released in near-surface layers and reach large size in particular on steep east, southeast and south facing slopes. &lt;br/> &lt;br/> In particular below approximately 2100 m and on very steep slopes gliding avalanches and moist snow slides are possible as the moisture increases.</comment>
    </avalancheActivity>
